name: final-critical-habitat-buffer-for-the-warner-sucker-catostomus-warnerensis
notes: These data shows estimated maximum and minimum areas where critical habitat may be designated on the shorelines of designated streams. Depending on stream width (ranging from a minimum of 15 ft to a maximum of 80 ft), buffers were created around Warner Sucker critical habitat stream centerlines resulting in a minimum area of 57.5 ft buffer for a 15 ft stream to a maximum of a 90 ft buffer for an 80 ft stream.
